<subSubSection lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="7" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="5.[826,1441,1511,1686]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
<emphasis box="[826,1006,1511,1533]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">New diagnosis:</emphasis>
Body oval in outline, size 
<emphasis box="[1356,1441,1512,1533]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">in vivo</emphasis>
25–40 ¥ 15–20 Mm; a small podite subterminally positioned; two contractile vacuoles situated on right side; one frontoventral kinety and three to five posterior fragments; nine to ten ventral kineties in postoral field; four to five terminal fragments; marine habitat.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[826,1441,1728,1903]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
<emphasis box="[826,1022,1728,1749]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Slide deposition:</emphasis>
